    <p>To install ZF packages with pyrus jump in your directory and run:</p>

    <div class="example"><pre><code class="highlight bash">
$ pyrus.phar .
$ pyrus.phar . channel-discover packages.zendframework.com
$ pyrus.phar . install zf2/<zf-package>
    </code></pre></div>

    <p>
        where <code>&lt;zf-package&gt;</code> is the package that you want to 
        install. You can install systemwide by omitting the "." in the above 
        examples. Alternately, you can specify a specific path instead of "." 
        (the current directory). The packages listed below may all be installed. 
        As an example:
    </p>

    <div class="example"><pre><code class="highlight bash">
$ pyrus.phar . install zf2/Zend_Http
    </code></pre></div>

    <p>
        To install the full standard distribution, use the "Zend_Framework" 
        metapackage, and indicate the "Standard" distribution, as follows:
    </p>

    <div class="example"><pre><code class="highlight bash">
$ pyrus.phar . install zf2/Zend_Framework#Standard
    </code></pre></div>
    
    <p>
        If you wish to install a non-stable version of that package,
        append the "-beta", "-rc" or "-devel" modifier prior to the "#" mark:
    </p>

    <div class="example"><pre><code class="highlight bash">
$ pyrus.phar . install zf2/Zend_Framework-beta#Standard
    </code></pre></div>

